- "Great" = demonstrated real business understanding through consistently good decisions
- "OK" = made reasonable decisions but missed obvious opportunities
- "Needs Work" = made decisions that show fundamental misunderstanding of profit, pricing, or supply management

Start with EXACTLY:
SCORES: Pricing Strategy:[Great/OK/Needs Work] | Supply Management:[Great/OK/Needs Work] | Weather Adaptation:[Great/OK/Needs Work] | Profit Maximization:[Great/OK/Needs Work] | Overall Business Acumen:[Great/OK/Needs Work]

Then 4 paragraphs of specific, encouraging-but-honest feedback:
1. Pricing — did they adapt price to weather and demand? Did they understand price elasticity (higher price = fewer customers)? Reference their actual average price and best/worst day.
2. Supply management — did they buy too much (waste) or too little (missed sales)? ${totalUnsold} cups unsold total. Did they learn from early mistakes?
3. Weather adaptation — did their decisions change on rainy vs hot days? Reference specific days.
4. Overall — connect to real business concepts: revenue, expenses, profit, break-even, supply and demand, opportunity cost. What is the single most important lesson from their 14 days?

Keep it conversational and specific. Reference their actual numbers. End with one piece of advice for running a real business based on what you observed. No markdown ** or ##.`;

  const userPrompt=`Student: ${state.playerName}
Game Result: ${netProfit>=0?'PROFIT':'LOSS'} of $${Math.abs(netProfit).toFixed(2)}
Started with: $${state.startingCash} (${state.loanAmount>0?`took $${state.loanAmount} loan`:'bootstrapped'})
